Package net.opentsdb.tsd

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractHttpQuery
    Abstract base class for HTTP queries.
    DropCachesRpc
    The "dropcaches" command.
    HistogramDataPointRpc
    The class responsible for writing histograms from Telnet calls or HTTP requests.
    HttpRpcPlugin
    A plugin that runs along side TSD's built-in HTTP endpoints (like the /api endpoints).
    HttpRpcPluginQuery
    Query class for HttpRpcPlugins.
    HttpSerializer
    Abstract base class for Serializers; plugins that handle converting requests and responses between OpenTSDB's internal data and various popular formats such as JSON, XML, OData, etc.
    PipelineFactory
    Creates a newly configured ChannelPipeline for a new channel.
    QueryExecutor
    TEMP class for handling V2 queries with expression support.
    RpcManager
    Manager for the lifecycle of HttpRpcs, TelnetRpcs, RpcPlugins, and HttpRpcPlugin.
    RpcPlugin
    The RPCPlugin allows for interacting with a TSD using different protocols such as Protobufs, Thrift, Memcache, anything folks want to create.
    RpcUtil  
    RTPublisher
    Real Time publisher plugin interface that is used to emit data from a TSD as data comes in.
    StatsRpc
    Handles fetching statistics from all over the code, collating them in a string buffer or list, and emitting them to the caller.
    StorageExceptionHandler
    This is a plugin for handling data points that fail the write to the underlying data store for various reasons.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BadRequestException
    Exception thrown by the HTTP handlers when presented with a bad request such as missing data, invalid requests, etc.
